  <div class="xhr_comment_body">
    <a style="font-weight:bold" href="/user/show/12925847-karen">Karen</a>

      
<span id="freeTextContainer3194758055269092240">Gina-Marie, yes, I think it is worth reading. Knowing about other genocides, the surrounding story of hate and scapegoating, and othering, is wise to </span>
  <span id="freeText3194758055269092240" style="display:none">Gina-Marie, yes, I think it is worth reading. Knowing about other genocides, the surrounding story of hate and scapegoating, and othering, is wise to study in my mind. You likely know much about the Armenian genocide, and thus the segments will add little to your knowledge about that first genocide of the 20th century. To me the need for these things to “never happen again” means we must continue to be reminded of how we fail to stand up when inhumanity happens.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3194758055269092240" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

